I honestly don't get why people are leaving negative reviews, this place is amazing. I got the 5 rolled tacos and they were the best ones I've ever had compared to their competitors. detailedReviews.text: Burrito was decent, enjoyable but nothing out of the ordinary. Price is a touch high. Service was friendly, and red salsa was pretty good.

detailedReviews.author: Frederick Asay
detailedReviews.text: Just opened, NOT going back.  Way to expensive$$$ for what you get.  Meal comes with a drink, BUT they have no drink dispenser so you pay for a drink and don't get one.  They replaced a Taco Time, even Taco Bell is better.  Oh and they did not have any water, had to go next door to get drinks and water.  All the neighborhood kids hang out there and buy their treats at the gas station and run around the restaurant yelling and screaming. For a fun time with noisy kids, this is your place.  5 stars for the fun.!!!!!  They also charge you a credit card fee.

detailedReviews.author: Jana Beckstead
detailedReviews.text: This place is terrible. I ordered a bean and cheese burrito, but when I got home, it was a cheese enchilada and the cheese wasn't even melted.

detailedReviews.author: Andrew G
detailedReviews.text: I got a carne asada burrito, which with their credit card fee ended up being almost $13. There was no beans or rice in the burrito, only a ton of moderately seasoned meat with a tiny bit of pico. The quality of the meat seemed barely above ground beef that got worse the more I ate. They didn't give enough green or red sauce, either. If it were cheaper or better tasting I might go back, but if I'm paying as much, if not more than Costa Vida or Cafe Rio for a smaller, worse tasting burrito I would rather go there. Service was good, though, and the guy was really friendly.
